{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-3vuu1","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-5lwo4","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-64xk6","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-858ub","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-d6nf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/CondProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CondRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads to wake up to collect the data."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is satisfied:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"C","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Whenever a thread calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now, it will wait until","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current_data is non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", i.e. until some other thread","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"race between the check of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" by the while loop in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"type":"text","text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to sleep atomically.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"true.  See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for an explanation of why the condition may","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_clear()"},{"text":" when done.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondRef"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondRef"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"CondRef","externalID":"s:4GLib7CondRefV"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"t